This paper deals with the evaluation of the quality of spatial data in databases, which is a core topic in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the impact of sampling on the quality of data, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of spatial data in decision making also has implications for cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and social impact (cs.SI).
